## Overview

This build started in september. I bought an [Airfix Douglas Dakota Mk.IV 1/72 kit](https://www.scalemates.com/kits/airfix-a08015-douglas-dakota-mkiv--258798) secondhand on a whim. Initially I was planning on building one of the variants included with the box, but after a visit to the Flygvapenmusem (air force musem) in Link√∂ping, I decided to "convert" it to a TP79 instead.

The kit is not the best I have ever built, both in terms of my skill and the kit quality (bent parts on the sprue for example), but there are some highlights. The panel lines, and (some of) the details are well defined.

